{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to summary-generation includes data from metrics, issue tracker, and deployment log.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at module handoff (three collectors -> aggregator -> summary input). A unit test of only the merge function can miss wiring/field-mapping regressions across modules. Real network/OS is not required because source adapters can be in-process fakes returning representative payloads. Higher levels rejected: System is disqualified because behavior text is about payload composition, not real HTTP/network effects; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because it does not evaluate model output, only what is passed in.","test_description":"Wire real collection/orchestration modules with fake source clients for the three inputs; run one report build; assert the exact summary-generation input contains required sections/keys from all three sources and preserves source attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"If one source is unavailable, report still generates with a \"data unavailable\" note for that section.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module error propagation and fallback rendering (collector failure -> orchestrator -> section note). In-process fakes that raise timeout/503 errors can reproduce the real failure boundary. Higher levels rejected: System is disqualified because real network outage is not required to validate fallback semantics; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because correctness does not depend on model judgment.","test_description":"Use real orchestrator/report composer with two successful fake sources and one failing fake source; assert process does not abort, report contains the unavailable marker only for the failed section, and other sections remain populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Narrative summary accurately represents key values in input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on the summary model’s semantic output quality (faithfulness to key values). Stubbed responses would always pass and hide real hallucination/omission errors. Workflow rejected: behavior describes one summary-generation decision, not multiple agentic stages chained together.","test_description":"Run the real summary-generation model on a fixed dataset with known key metrics/issues/deployments; score output for factual inclusion and numeric consistency against ground truth (e.g., required key-value checks/tolerance rubric) across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"End-to-end report (collection through email delivery) reaches configured recipient inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure boundary is infrastructure: real HTTP/API connectivity plus actual email delivery path and inbox receipt. In-process mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, transport, formatting, and delivery integration failures. Agentic rejected: behavior text checks delivery-to-inbox success, not quality of model decisions; a deterministic summary fixture can satisfy this behavior while still testing the true delivery boundary.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled run in a production-like environment against reachable test instances of all three data sources and a real test mailbox; assert one complete email is delivered to configured recipients with expected subject/body structure and attached/embedded report content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.65,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If email service is unreachable, save report locally and retry delivery on next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure is orchestration/state persistence across runs (send failure -> local save -> next-run retry). This can be reproduced with a failing email client fake plus real local filesystem persistence. System rejected: behavior does not require real network stack behavior to validate retry/state logic. Agentic/Workflow rejected because no model-output correctness is under test.","test_description":"Run pipeline with real retry/persistence modules, fake mailer that fails first run then succeeds second run; assert fallback file is written after first failure, consumed on next run, and email send is retried and succeeds without data loss/duplication.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.28,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
